Sign up for email alerts for Nauru travel advice
Most visits to Nauru are trouble-free. Accommodation options are limited. We recommend that you plan flights and book accommodation well in advance of travel.
Although there’s no recent history of terrorism in Nauru, attacks can’t be ruled out. See Terrorism
There’s no British Consulate in Nauru. Consular support is severely limited, however, the British High Commission Honiara in Solomon Islands can provide some consular support to British nationals.
Take out comprehensive travel and medical insurance before you travel.
